\f0\b Supabase has a default 1,000-row limit
\f1\b0  on all .select() queries. Must paginate via .range() for any aggregation. Discovered after merge made data large enough to hit the limit.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b clinics.slug is NOT NULL
\f1\b0  \'97 any INSERT into clinics MUST include a slug. Forgot this in migration v1, had to add inline slug generation in v2.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Google Places returns noise even with location bias
\f1\b0  \'97 ~3% of "IV therapy" search results were actually urgent cares, hospitals, ERs, or even Whole Foods. Filter by name patterns post-merge.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b NPI data is fundamentally consumer-mismatched
\f1\b0  for wellness IV directories. Places discovery yielded 99% directory-relevant results vs NPI's 3.3%.\
{\listtext	0.	}
\f0\b Pagination + filter triple = the standard query pattern
\f1\b0  for this codebase going forward. Document in CLAUDE2.md.\
